		<h1>EGYPT</h1>
		<p>
			<strong>Egypt</strong>, officially known as the Arab Republic of Egypt, is a unique transcontinental country located in the northeastern corner of Africa and the southwestern corner of Asia. It is connected by the Sinai Peninsula, which serves as a bridge between the two continents. To the north, Egypt is bordered by the Mediterranean Sea, providing access to key trade routes and a rich maritime history. The eastern border is defined by the Red Sea, while to the south, Egypt shares a boundary with Sudan, and to the west, it is bordered by Libya. In the northeast, the country shares borders with Palestine and Israel. The Gulf of Aqaba in the northeast acts as a natural separation between Egypt and the nations of Jordan and Saudi Arabia.

			Cairo, the nation’s capital, is the largest city and a cultural and political hub, steeped in history and modern significance. Alexandria, the second-largest city, lies along the Mediterranean coast and plays a vital role as an industrial and tourism center, blending historical landmarks with modern developments. With a population of approximately 110 million people, Egypt ranks as the 14th most populous country in the world and the third most populous in Africa. The country’s strategic location, rich history, and cultural heritage make it a central player in the region, connecting continents and civilizations through centuries.
		</p>

